From 8806751d51e5e3a424db586fe2aa1f482bc22433 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: keke142 <jdkeke142@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 16:03:33 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] Fix window size callback not firing on unset fullscreen

When exiting fullscreen via _glfwSetWindowSizeWayland, the window
surface is resized but the size callback is never fired. The client
(e.g. Minecraft) keeps the old fullscreen dimensions cached, causing
input coordinate mismatches until a manual resize.

Add _glfwInputWindowSize after the resize so clients are always
notified of the new dimensions.

Based on BoyOrigin/glfw-wayland patch 0004.
---
 src/wl_window.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/wl_window.c b/src/wl_window.c
index 127d46c..80ff9d8 100644
--- a/src/wl_window.c
+++ b/src/wl_window.c
@@ -2989,6 +2989,8 @@ void _glfwSetWindowSizeWayland(_GLFWwindow* window, int width, int height)
             libdecor_state_free(frameState);
         }
 
+        _glfwInputWindowSize(window, width, height);
+
         if (window->wl.visible)
             _glfwInputWindowDamage(window);
     }
